{"word":"εὐαής","slug":"εὐαής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐαής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-ᾱής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄημι'><el>ἄημι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>well ventilated, fresh, airy</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a>, of a wind, <i>favourably blowing, fair</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: —<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>favourable</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}